The paper deals with the automatic digitizing of paper maps using deep learning techniques, specifically semantic segmentation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The use of deep learning models such as U-Net also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed method on GPGPU and cuDNN, indicating the use of deep learning frameworks and libraries, which falls under the deep learning (cs.DL) sub-category.
